page.title: 09WOODLAND
page.content: In this part, woodland is not an important feature of the landscape, most of which consists of large cultivated fields. Near Wester Kincaple, there is a small area of deciduous wood. Elsewhere there were a few copses and some shelter belts of coniferous. Most of the large trees are clusterd round farm houses. Especially noticeable are those in the ground of Kincaple House where many trees planted 150 years ago are about 30m high. Beech, sycomore, and some exotic conifers are the main species. there is little new planting to replace the older trees; it seems that this countryside will become less wooded in future.
